### Create Patient 1 (Palghar - Dengue prone)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/patients
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ayushi",
  "age": 20,
  "gender": "Female",
  "language": "Tamil",
  "district": "Palghar"
}

###

### Update Patient 1 (Update age to 21 and language to English)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/patients/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "age": 21,
  "language": "English"
}

###

### Get All Patients
GET http://localhost:8080/api/patients

###

### 1. Test Emergency Case (Unconscious)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cases/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "language": "Hindi",
  "fever": true,
  "unconscious": true
}

###

### 2. Test Routine Case (TB Diagnosis match: fever + cough > 14 days)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cases/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fever": true,
  "cough": true,
  "coughDurationDays": 15,
  "breathlessness": false,
  "unconscious": false
}

### 

### 3. Test Routine Case (Viral Fever match: fever only)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cases/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fever": true,
  "cough": false,
  "unconscious": false
}

###

### 4. Create multiple cases in Palghar to trigger Outbreak Spike (> 5 cases)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/cases/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fever": true
}

### Go click 4 above multiple times to trigger the outbreak logic

### 5. Get Analytics: Case Summary
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/case-summary

###

### 6. Get Analytics: Outbreaks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/outbreaks

###

### 7. Get Patient History
GET http://localhost:8080/api/patients/1/history

